⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Guardians & Divine Beasts
node ZEL · ZEL · ⟦The Guardians & Divine Beasts:ZEL:0bb3c9⟧

WHO   — The Guardians & Divine Beasts — the Ancient Machines
WHAT  — Ancient autonomous weapons of a lost age — the spider-legged Guardians with their searching blue-then-red beams, and the colossal Divine Beasts Vah Ruta, Vah Rudania, Vah Medoh, and Vah Naboris, terraforming engines of war meant to bleed the Calamity dry.
WHERE — ZEL · The Legend of Zelda  Framework inputs: The Legend of Zelda (the saga entire)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because mortals alone could not stand against a force reborn from age to age; because the Sheikah poured their genius into machines that would not tire, would not falter, and would wait ten thousand years in the earth for the day the darkness returned.
HOW   — By tireless legs and turret eyes, by laser beams that lock and burn, by the elemental fury of four titans — water, fire, wind, and lightning — and by ancient cores that endure across millennia, for good when guided and for ruin when seized.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  We are the engines of the ancient ones — built to slay the Calamity, and turned, when taken, against the land we were made to save.

